  "prompt": "What are some smart questions to ask a CEO over a lunch meeting?",
  "response": "Here are some thoughtful questions to ask a CEO during a lunch meeting:\n\n1. Professional Strategy Questions:\n- What strategic challenges are you currently focusing on?\n- How do you see the industry evolving in the next 3-5 years?\n- What emerging technologies or trends excite you most?\n\n2. Leadership & Personal Development:\n- What leadership lessons have been most impactful in your career?\n- How do you maintain work-life balance?\n- What advice would you give to someone aspiring to a leadership role?\n\n3. Company Culture & Vision:\n- What core values drive your organization?\n- How do you foster innovation within your team?\n- What are the most significant opportunities you see for the company?\n\n4. Personal Insight Questions:\n- What motivated you to pursue this career path?\n- Who were your most important mentors?\n- What's the most challenging decision you've had to make as a CEO?\n\n5. Learning & Growth:\n- What books or resources have influenced your leadership philosophy?\n- How do you continually develop your skills?\n- What do you wish you knew earlier in your career?\n\n6. Forward-Looking Questions:\n- What's your long-term vision for the company?\n- How are you preparing for potential market disruptions?\n\nRemember to be genuinely curious, listen actively, and engage in a conversational manner.",
